1 or volunteer as provided in KRS 160.145;
2 (c) The diagnosis or treatment of a minor by a health care provider in a health
3 care facility;
4 (d) Communicating with a minor to determine if the minor is dependent,
5 neglected, or abused;
6 (e) Age-appropriate conversations about puberty and human sexuality with a
7 minor by the minor's parent or guardian; and
8 (f) Any conversation with a minor that is part of a person's job-related duties.
9 Section 2. KRS 510.010 is amended to read as follows:
10 The following definitions apply in this chapter unless the context otherwise requires:
11 (1) "Adult intermediary" means a person who is eighteen (18) years of age or older
12 and communicates with another for the purpose of procuring or promoting the
13 use of a minor in violation of KRS 510.155;
14 (2) "Course of conduct" means a pattern of conduct composed of two (2) or more
15 acts, evidencing a continuity of purpose;
16 (3) "Deviate sexual intercourse" means any act of sexual gratification involving the sex
17 organs of one person and the mouth or anus of another; or penetration of the anus of
18 one person by any body part or a foreign object manipulated by another person.
19 "Deviate sexual intercourse" does not include penetration of the anus by any body
20 part or a foreign object in the course of the performance of generally recognized
21 health-care practices;
22 (4)[(2)] "Forcible compulsion" means physical force or threat of physical force,
23 express or implied, which places a person in fear of immediate death, physical
24 injury to self or another person, fear of the immediate kidnap of self or another
25 person, or fear of any offense under this chapter. Physical resistance on the part of
26 the victim shall not be necessary to meet this definition;
27 (5) "Foreign object" means anything used in commission of a sexual act other than
